5:
Aaand that should do it, Hao. Let's
get goi—Wait, Hao?
12:
Hey, Meow-Meow! What are those?
They look cold and stiff...
16:
Stop callin' me "Meow-Meow!" I have
a name, and it's NIMBUS.
18:
Besides, isn't that what you call the
toy cat on your belt? We can't both
be Meow-Meow.
21: Sure you can. You look exactly alike!
28: Anyways. Let's get back to Alk and—
41: A little girl was... was... Ngh! I have to—
45:
To get some rest, idiot. Someone
else, what's going on?!
48:
A man just kidnapped a child! The
girl there tried to stop him, but—
55:
Stella... Damn it! There's too many
people here for me to pick up a
scent—
66:
The winds will lead the hunt. And
when I find him...
74:
*panting* Tch... I ain't lettin' it end
like this!
78: Shut up! Can it, or I'll—
83:
I won't let you get away with this.
...Your spirit must rejoin the winds.
93:
Why did stop me? I finally caught
my prey, and—
105: Me? But I wasn't... I was just—
108: Mom! It's not what it looks like...
119:
Thankfully, the wounds were pretty
shallow, but we've got her
bandaged up and resting just to be
safe.
121:
If anything, she was more worried
about you, Hao. You doing okay?
125: No... No need to worry about me.
131:
Just... Do you think the woman who
helped the little girl was her mother?
139:
She was afraid of me, but... she was
a strong human.
142:
Forget about it. Today was one hell
of a day, and we're all beat.
145:
Hey. Look, I don't know HOW many
times I have to tell you, but I'm not
your stuffed cat.
148:
I know. I know you're not
Meow-Meow, and Starview isn't the
forest.
151:
But it all feels... familiar. Like
something long ago—something I
can't remember.
153:
Like the person who gave me...
Meow-Meow...
158: Wait, did he just fall asleep?
166:
C'mon, it won't hurt you to humor
him a little. Okay, "Meow-Meow?"
169:
All right, all right, but don't YOU get
started with all that Meow-Meow
stuff.
